Here is a quick summary of Jumpstart Payments for your knowledge:

1.  We formed Jumpstart Payments so we would have a "backup plan" if things didn't
    work out with Card Connect and First Data. We needed to set ourselves up as an
    ISO to help build our future and not be subject to getting stuck in a corner.

	Currently doing payments with Card Connect / First Data.
	Currently have about 6,000 Accounts.

2.	CardConnect Issue with us ended up getting resolved, but still want to have multiple
processing companies for the future, to have options for the future both with
payments, software and other services.

3. We will be moving business to another processor and gateway in an "organized"
fashion over the next 1-2 years as customer contracts expire.

Our main goal is to get better pricing and service, and have more flexibility in the
future if we need to do more than 1 company at a time.

4. Since we are an ISO, our agreement allows us to offer processing services to other
companies that may not have a good payment solution. It is also setup to process
internet businesses, CBD products, and other business types.

5. Would really like to have the $3 Fee taken off from Manager Vault.

	- Currently paying $3 plus basis points.
	- Would like to just pay basis points.
	- We are paying a cost to access your system like Restaurant Manager, Dinerware,
	  Future POS, etc.

6.	Have a couple small integrations we would like to complete, but not a huge priority
right now.

Let me know if you need more information, and thank you for listening.

Thanks,

JD,

Here is a quick summary of Jumpstart Payments for your knowledge:

  1.  We formed Jumpstart Payments so we would have a "backup plan" if things didn't work out with Card Connect
        and First Data. We needed to set ourselves up as an ISO to help build our future and not be subject to getting
        stuck in a corner.

      *   Currently doing payments with Card Connect / First Data.
      *   Currently have about 6,000 Accounts.
  2.  CardConnect Issue with us ended up getting resolved, but still want to have multiple processing companies for the
      future, to have options for the future both with payments, software and other services.
  3.  We will be moving business to another processor and gateway in an "organized" fashion over the next 1-2 years
      as customer contracts expire.

Our main goal is to get better pricing and service, and have more flexibility in the future if we
need to do more than 1 company at a time.

  4.   Since we are an ISO, our agreement allows us to offer processing services to other companies that may not
        have a good payment solution. It is also setup to process internet businesses, CBD products, and other
        business types.

  5.  Would really like to have the $3 Fee taken off from Manager Vault.
      *   Currently paying $3 plus basis points.
      *   Would like to just pay basis points.
      *   We are paying a cost to access your system like Restaurant Manager, Dinerware, Future POS, etc.
  6.  Have a couple small integrations we would like to complete, but not a huge priority right now.
Let me know if you need more information, and thank you for listening.
Thanks,
